<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="581" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,942,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">
Worldwide in distribution, this family has over 250 species, primarily in tropical regions. In the Neotropics there are over 120 species, all in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Siebold" authorityYear="1856" box="[587,738,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Helicopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[587,738,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">Helicopsyche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The other genus in this family, 
<taxonomicName authority="McFarlane 1973" authorityName="McFarlane" authorityYear="1973" box="[1116,1404,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Rakiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1206,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">Rakiura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McFarlane, A. G." box="[1215,1404,979,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="23 - 34" refId="ref6162" refString="McFarlane, A. G. (1973) Five new species of Trichoptera from New Zealand. Journal of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 3 (1), 23 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03036758.1973.10416100" type="journal article" year="1973">McFarlane 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[282,432,1015,1041]" name="New Zealand" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
